<heading bold="true" box="[151,844,151,177]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,844,151,177]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chamorro &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,439,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guyanae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,439,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Polyplectropus guyanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, newly recognized
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1436,226,492]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
This newly established group includes 2 new species and is characterized by the combined possession of the following traits (
<figureCitation box="[346,445,266,292]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="127.[151,255,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[220,1366,200,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-77@127.[220,1366,197,1747]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 62. Male genitalia of Polyplectropus guyanae, new species (holotype): A—left lateral view and inset of mesoventral process of preanal appendage; B—dorsal view; C—caudal view; D—ventral view; E–H—phallus: E—left lateral view; F—dorsal view; G—apex dorsal view; (paratype): H—apex, caudal view." pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Figs. 62</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[457,490,266,292]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="128.[151,255,1922,1946]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,551,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-164@128.[220,1367,551,1895]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURE 63. Male genitalia of Polyplectropus peruvianus, new species (holotype): A—left lateral view and inset of mesoventral process of left preanal appendage; B—dorsal view; C—caudal view; D—ventral view; E–H—phallus: E— left lateral view; F—dorsal view; G—apex, ventral view; H—apex, caudal view." pageId="126" pageNumber="127">63</figureCitation>
):
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="126" pageNumber="127" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1436,226,492]" box="[151,1063,306,332]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">1. Dorsal digitate lobe on the mesoventral process of the preanal appendage;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1436,226,492]" box="[151,951,346,372]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">2. Presence of peg-like spines in the phallic endothecal membrane;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1436,226,492]" box="[151,888,386,412]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">3. Oblong intermediate appendage with a pair of apical setae;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1436,226,492]" box="[151,901,426,452]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">4. Absence of a dorsolateral process of the preanal appendage;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1436,226,492]" box="[151,764,466,492]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">5. Clavate dorsal branch of the inferior appendage.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
